            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> you are requesting a way to NOT activate the LSP server.\n\nCorrect, that's what `single_file_support = false` does. It says \"if none of the root markers are found (i.e. there is no root dir), do not launch the server.\"\n\nThe current behavior of `vim.lsp.enable()` is to launch the server with a nil root dir if no root marker is matched, similar to `single_file_support = true`.\n\nPerhaps the new title is more clear?",
