            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I think this is reasonable enough to support. Lspconfig already had first class support for it, and it seems all we need to add is a single boolean field to `vim.lsp.Config` to indicate whether we should attach if no root dirs can be found. This Boolean can then be specified by the user in the `*` config to apply globally, and then also set in specific server configs for servers that don't support it.\n\nI'm assuming the current default (effectively `single_file_support=true`) should remain?",
