        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "As far as defaults, lspconfig has 183 LSPs with `single_file_support = true` as their default and 5 with `false`. So I think keeping the current default makes sense.\n\nI'm guessing lspconfig chose the default based on whether the LSP works at all; I assume those 5 LSPs completely break without a rootdir. This new flag would allow the user to handle both this case (LSP doesn't work at all without a rootdir) and the case I described originally (LSP can successfully launch but would not be useful, like clangd).",
